Add these lines to the preamble (before `\begin{document}`):

```latex
\usepackage{graphicx}
```

Then, on your title page or where you want the logo, add:

```latex
\begin{center}
  \includegraphics[width=0.3\textwidth]{logo.png}
\end{center}
```

**Full minimal example for a title page:**

```latex
\documentclass{report}
\usepackage{graphicx}
\begin{document}
\begin{titlepage}
    \begin{center}
        \vspace*{2cm}
        {\LARGE\bfseries Your Thesis Title}\\[2cm]
        \includegraphics[width=0.3\textwidth]{logo.png}\\[1cm]
        {\large Your Name}\\
        {\large Institute Name}
    \end{center}
\end{titlepage}
\end{document}
```

Just replace `logo.png` with the actual file name if it‚Äôs different. Make sure the image file is in the same folder as your `.tex` file, then compile.

